  "tags": null,
  "notes": "Table saison inspired by Hitachino Nest Saison du Japon and Saison Dupont. Low ABV but drinks bigger than its gravity. High mash temp for body, structured fermentation ramp for glycerol and phenol production. Brew on Ss Brewtech SVBS.\n\nMethod: Full-volume no-sparge BIAB as recommended by Ss Brewtech for SVBS. All water goes into mash, lift basket and drain. Lower efficiency (~62%) but simpler brew day.\n\nWater: Distilled + CaCl2 only (5.5g in full volume). Target: Ca 48, Cl 85.\n\nFermentation: Start cool (68F/20C), ramp 3-4F/day to 78-80F (25.6-26.7C). M29 doesn't need extreme temps like 3724.\n\nDry hop Hallertau Blanc for 3 days max. High carbonation (3.0-3.2 vol) is critical.",

